        <p><em>Last updated: 25 June 2026</em></p>
 
        <h2>What this site is</h2>
        <p>The Attaché Desk is an independent editorial website. Its guides and articles are written as orientation resources for diplomats, consular staff and international officials preparing for or managing a posting abroad. The content is researched from publicly available official sources, which are cited in each guide.</p>
 
        <h2>What this site is not</h2>
        <p>Nothing on this site constitutes legal, tax, administrative, security or professional advice of any kind. The guides do not recommend or encourage any specific course of action. They do not replace the guidance of your mission, your sending organisation, qualified legal or tax advisers, or the relevant national authorities. If you are making a decision with legal, financial or administrative consequences, consult a qualified professional.</p>
 
        <h2>Accuracy and currency</h2>
        <p>The Attaché Desk makes reasonable efforts to keep its guides current and to cite accurate official sources. Regulations, procedures and entitlements change. The information on this site may not reflect the most recent developments in every jurisdiction. Always verify the current position with the relevant official authority before acting on anything you read here.</p>
 
        <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>The content of this site, including its text, structure and editorial selections, is the property of Anthony Rocco and The Attaché Desk. Reproduction, redistribution or commercial use without prior written permission is not permitted. Linking to pages on this site is welcome.</p>
 
        <h2>External links</h2>
        <p>This site links to official government websites, international organisations, and other third-party sources. These links are provided for reference only. The Attaché Desk is not responsible for the content, accuracy or availability of third-party websites and does not endorse any product, service or organisation linked from this site.</p>
 
        <h2>Affiliate relationships</h2>
        <p>This site currently has no commercial or affiliate relationships with any organisation, school, insurer, or other third party mentioned in its guides. If affiliate links or sponsored content are introduced in the future, they will be clearly identified as such at the point of publication.</p>
 
        <h2>No warranties</h2>
        <p>This site is provided on an "as is" basis. The Attaché Desk makes no warranty, express or implied, regarding the completeness, accuracy, reliability or suitability of the information it contains. Use of this site is at your own discretion.</p>
 
        <h2>Governing law</h2>
        <p>These terms are governed by the laws of Gibraltar. Any dispute arising from the use of this site will be subject to the non-exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Gibraltar.</p>
 
        <h2>Contact and corrections</h2>
        <p>For editorial queries, corrections or other matters: <a href="mailto:contact@theattachedesk.com">contact@theattachedesk.com</a></p>
        <p>If you identify an error or an outdated reference in any guide, corrections are welcome. Write to the address above with the page concerned, the inaccuracy, and a reference to the correct current source where possible.</p>
 
